text: It is confusing that there are dots on both the left and right side of the task names in execute mode. Please show the task status indicator on the left side of the title. On the right side, only show assignee.

proposedTasks.title: Reorganize task row layout: status left, assignee right
proposedTasks.description:
In the Execute tab epic card task list, the status indicator dot and the assignee dot both appear on each side of the task title, causing visual confusion. Refactor the task row component so that:

- The status badge/dot is displayed exclusively on the LEFT side of the task title.
- The assignee indicator is displayed exclusively on the RIGHT side of the task title.
- No duplicate indicators appear on both sides.

Acceptance criteria:
1. Each task row shows exactly one status indicator, positioned to the left of the task title.
2. Each task row shows the assignee (if any) on the right side of the task title.
3. No colored dots or badges appear on the same side as the other indicator.
4. All task states (Planning, Backlog, Ready, In Progress, In Review, Done, Blocked) render correctly in the left-side position.
5. Unassigned tasks show no assignee element on the right (no empty dot or placeholder).

taskTitles: Reorganize task row layout: status left, assignee right
